# InfraFlux v2.0 - Technology Stack and Provider Patterns

## 🏭 **Core Technology Stack**

### **Infrastructure Platform**
- **Proxmox VE** - Virtualization platform (v7.0+)
- **Talos Linux** - Immutable Kubernetes OS (v1.10.4+)
- **Pulumi** - Infrastructure as Code engine
- **TypeScript** - Primary programming language

### **Pulumi Providers**
- **@muhlba91/pulumi-proxmoxve** (v6.2.0+) - Proxmox VE management
- **@pulumiverse/talos** (v0.5.2+) - Talos cluster management
- **@pulumi/kubernetes** (v4.8.0+) - Kubernetes resource management
- **@worawat/flux** (v1.0.1+) - FluxCD GitOps integration

## 🔧 **Proxmox VE Integration Patterns**

### **Provider Configuration**
```typescript
const proxmoxProvider = new proxmox.Provider('proxmox', {
  endpoint: config.proxmox.endpoint,
  username: config.proxmox.username, // format: 'user@realm'
  password: config.proxmox.password,
  insecure: config.proxmox.insecure, // true for self-signed certs
});
```

### **ISO File Management**
Reference [src/components/cloud-image-template.ts](mdc:src/components/cloud-image-template.ts):
```typescript
// Download ISO with integrity checking
const talosISO = new proxmox.download.File('talos-iso', {
  contentType: 'iso',
  datastoreId: 'local', // ISO storage pool
  nodeName: config.proxmox.node,
  url: 'https://factory.talos.dev/image/...',
  fileName: 'talos-v1.10.4-custom.iso',
});
```

### **VM Template Creation**
```typescript
// Create template with ISO attached
const template = new proxmox.vm.VirtualMachine('template', {
  nodeName: config.proxmox.node,
  vmId: 9010, // Safe template ID range
  template: true, // Mark as template

  // Attach Talos ISO to CD-ROM
  cdrom: {
    enabled: true,
    fileId: talosISO.id,
    interface: 'ide2',
  },

  // Enable QEMU Guest Agent
  agent: {
    enabled: true,
    trim: true,
    type: 'virtio',
  },
});
```

### **VM Cloning Pattern**
```typescript
// Clone from template (faster than installation)
const vm = new proxmox.vm.VirtualMachine('vm', {
  clone: {
    nodeName: config.proxmox.node,
    vmId: template.vmId, // Source template
    full: true, // Full clone
  },

  // Hardware specs
  cpu: { cores: 2, type: 'host' },
  memory: { dedicated: 4096 },

  // Storage configuration
  disks: [{
    interface: 'scsi0',
    datastoreId: 'local-lvm', // VM storage pool
    size: 30, // GB
    fileFormat: 'raw',
  }],
});
```

## 🐧 **Talos Linux Integration**

### **Image Factory Configuration**
```typescript
// Custom schematic with extensions
const schematic = 'ec83aa8b78f86413fceed33b6f16f598df0e3c4b1cbd514c5790364b49d4f8f6';
const extensions = ['qemu-guest-agent', 'cloudflared'];
const installerImage = `factory.talos.dev/nocloud-installer/${schematic}:v1.10.4`;
```

### **Machine Configuration Pattern**
Reference [src/components/talos-cluster.ts](mdc:src/components/talos-cluster.ts):
```typescript
// Generate machine configuration
const machineConfig = talos.machine.getConfigurationOutput({
  clusterName: 'homelab',
  machineType: 'controlplane', // or 'worker'
  clusterEndpoint: 'https://192.168.1.200:6443',
  machineSecrets: secrets.machineSecrets,
});

// Apply with custom patches
const configApply = new talos.machine.ConfigurationApply('config', {
  clientConfiguration: secrets.clientConfiguration,
  machineConfigurationInput: machineConfig.machineConfiguration,
  node: '192.168.1.200',
  configPatches: [
    pulumi.jsonStringify({
      machine: {
        install: {
          disk: '/dev/vda',
          image: installerImage, // Custom factory image
        },
        network: {
          hostname: 'master-0',
          interfaces: [{
            interface: 'eth0',
            addresses: ['192.168.1.200/24'],
            routes: [{ network: '0.0.0.0/0', gateway: '192.168.1.1' }],
          }],
        },
      },
    }),
  ],
});
```

### **Cluster Bootstrap**
```typescript
// Bootstrap first control plane
const bootstrap = new talos.machine.Bootstrap('bootstrap', {
  node: masterIP,
  clientConfiguration: secrets.clientConfiguration,
});

// Generate kubeconfig
const kubeconfig = new talos.cluster.Kubeconfig('kubeconfig', {
  node: masterIP,
  clientConfiguration: secrets.clientConfiguration,
});
```

## 🌐 **Network Discovery Patterns**

### **QEMU Guest Agent Integration**
Reference [src/components/network-discovery.ts](mdc:src/components/network-discovery.ts):
```typescript
// Use native VM outputs for network info
const vmNetworkInfo = vm.apply(vm => ({
  vmId: vm.vmId,
  macAddresses: vm.macAddresses,
  ipv4Addresses: vm.ipv4Addresses, // Real-time from guest agent
  ipv6Addresses: vm.ipv6Addresses,
  networkInterfaceNames: vm.networkInterfaceNames,
}));
```

### **Proxmox Bridge Auto-Discovery**
```typescript
// Discover network config from Proxmox
const networkInfo = proxmox.network.getHostsOutput({
  nodeName: config.proxmox.node,
});

const bridgeConfig = networkInfo.apply(info => ({
  gateway: info.gateway, // Auto-discovered
  subnet: info.subnet,   // Auto-discovered
  bridge: 'vmbr0',
}));
```

## 🔄 **GitOps Integration (FluxCD)**

### **FluxCD Bootstrap Pattern**
Reference [src/components/gitops.ts](mdc:src/components/gitops.ts):
```typescript
// Generate SSH key for Git access
const sshKey = new tls.PrivateKey('flux-ssh', {
  algorithm: 'ECDSA',
  ecdsaCurve: 'P256',
});

// Create Flux provider
const fluxProvider = new flux.Provider('flux', {
  git: {
    url: gitOpsConfig.repoUrl,
    branch: 'main',
    ssh: {
      username: 'git',
      privateKey: sshKey.privateKeyPem,
    },
  },
});

// Bootstrap Flux
const fluxBootstrap = new flux.FluxBootstrapGit('bootstrap', {
  path: 'clusters/homelab',
  interval: '5m',
  components: [
    'source-controller',
    'kustomize-controller',
    'helm-controller',
    'notification-controller',
  ],
});
```

## 💾 **Storage Management Patterns**

### **Dual Storage Strategy**
```typescript
// Storage configuration
const storageConfig = {
  // Fast storage for VMs (SSDs, NVMe, LVM)
  vmStorage: 'local-lvm',

  // Slower/cheaper storage for ISOs (HDDs, directory)
  isoStorage: 'local',

  // Disk format optimization
  diskFormat: 'raw', // Better performance than qcow2
};
```

### **Resource Organization**
```typescript
// VM ID ranges for organization
const idRanges = {
  masters: 8000,     // 8000-8099
  workers: 8100,     // 8100-8199
  templates: 9010,   // 9010+ for templates
};

// Template specialization
const templateTypes = {
  master: {
    cores: 2,
    memory: 4096,
    diskSize: 30, // GB
    optimizedFor: 'control-plane',
  },
  worker: {
    cores: 2,
    memory: 4096,
    diskSize: 50, // GB - more space for workloads
    optimizedFor: 'workloads',
  },
};
```

